    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-26T18:02:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-26T18:02:00-05:00" n="875"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/8–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 875<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d875fn1">Sent also to Amman, Jerusalem, and Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-26T19:02:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1954—7:02 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. Amman’s 60<note n="2" xml:id="d875fn2">Not printed.</note> Tel Aviv’s
                        192<note n="3" xml:id="d875fn3">
                        <ref target="#d869">Document 869</ref>.</note> Cairo’s 203.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d875fn4">
                        <ref target="#d861">Document 861</ref>.</note> Tel Aviv requested approach
                        <persName corresp="#p_DBGM1">Dayan</persName> reporting that our initial
                    soundings in Cairo and Amman indicate willingness for commanders to meet. We
                    suggest first meetings be held between commanders <gloss target="#t_Jlem1"
                        >Jlem</gloss> sector and Gaza frontiers. In our view agenda should be
                    limited discussion border security measures and to setting up means for further
                    periodic contacts with view reduction border incidents. Arrangements could be
                    made regarding place and time meeting through <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1"
                        >UNTSO</gloss> observers. It should be made clear that what we are seeking
                    is resumption commanders meetings which as in past would be held informally and
                    outside framework <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                        >FYI</gloss> while we would hope such meetings might improve atmosphere to
                    degree where Israel would see value resuming full cooperation with <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> feel would be counter-productive attempt link
                    these meetings with <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> participation at this
                    time.</p>
                <p>Tel Aviv requested consult closely with <gloss target="#t_ConGen1">ConGen</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Jlem1">Jlem</gloss> and at appropriate time <gloss
                        target="#t_ConGen1">ConGen</gloss> should provide background to <gloss
                        target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Cairo and Amman requested make similar approaches <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1"
                        >Gohar</persName> and Arab Legion.</p>
                <p>Report developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
